    <abstract>
      <t>Certain traffic engineering path computation problems require solutions that consist of multiple traffic paths, that together form a solution. Returning just one single traffic path does not provide a valid solution. This document defines a mechanism to encode multiple paths for a single set of objectives and constraints. This is a generic PCEP mechanism, not specific to any path setup type or dataplane. The mechanism is applicable to both stateless and stateful PCEP.</t>
